🚀 Day 27 of #100DaysOfCode Challenge! 🚀

Today, I explored how web requests work behind the scenes! 🌐💻
✅ Learned about DNS, HTTP, and how browsers fetch and render websites.
✅ Understood the role of Load Balancers in handling high traffic.

✅ Discovered how CDNs improve website speed and efficiency.
✅ Explored Web Application Firewalls (WAFs) and their role in cybersecurity.
✅ Studied Web Servers, including Apache, Nginx, and IIS, and their handling of static vs. dynamic content.

It’s fascinating to see how all these components work together to make the internet function smoothly! 🔥

